Grpahics, story, user friendly, NPC interactions make this game great. When 
playing this game there is no rush or no pressure to spend real money. 
Developers did a great job on this game. Four dislikes: 1. Using my other 
heroes in battle with main hero costs an unreasonable amount of field 
points (those heroes are much needed in New Game Plus 3, but I can't afford 
a 400-600 point hero). 2. Game sometimes crashes at worst times when I am 
close to winning (I have Note 8). 3. The games doesn't increase field 
points when playing New Game Plus(enemies are harder and my army still is 
limited to a small size at castle defense). 4. There are no increase unit's 
abilities to keep up with New Game Plus enemies (you will get slaughtered 
by high enemy numbers and harder enemies). Seriously, New Game Plus 
requires rebalancing. I am at New Game Plus 3, and it's hard. I gave up on 
game at castle defense wave 31...it's impossible. Try castle defense wave 
31 of New Game Plus 3, and you will see how hard it is, you will get owned. 
Also, would be nice to upgrade current items or combine Runes. Is there a 
way devs can reasonably rebalance the game to accommodate higher levels of 
New Game Plus? Is it even worth going past New Game Plus 2? Would it be ok 
to have the Bannerman unit produce starting points equal to the level of 
New Game Plus? For example, New Game Plus 2 means Bannerman produces at 
starting rate of 2.

The game is extremely fun, however there are only a few things that keep it from being 5 stars. Having to actually travel to lands you've already gotten to get treasure is a pain in the ass. Second of all, there's not many good army compositions besides getting The Elite, getting 4 captains, and just winning the game. One other feature that would be greatly appreciated is more mission types. As of right now, there's only skirmish, defend, siege, and  defend/siege. They all pretty much play the same, with little variety. Some other mission types, such as retrieval, where you have to move things from the battlefield back to the base, or maybe something like hard point, where you must defend certain areas on the battlefield. While the controls aren't amazing, they're definitely usable for mobile, and definitely the some of the best for phones.

It crashes from time to time. Normally get an error at start-up, program is not working properly (not a quote, my phone is off right now) and to "wait" or close on M. If I press close, well, it closes. If I "wait," it allows me to play the game, although it may crash later. Also got errors maybe once a day on 5.1.1.   --- As a positive, the Devs re-tweaked the visual settings, as such, I now can use the game with *some* medium settings which improve aesthetics, so better than before. Endless is great although by the 28+ minute, it gets unplayable due to lag.   So, it is still buggy, but damn you Devs, great skill on "still" crafting a really well balanced game. Not the deepest like an RPG, yet  with enough replay potential,  action, a bit of rogue elements that even with the crashes, I still recommend the purchase. It IS a lot of fun. Playing in 5.1.1 and 6.

Easily 5/5 stands out from the piles of pay to win crap on mobile. You don't need to buy anything besides the game (you could but you can easily farm 30 crystals aka $1 worth after capturing half the areas in a half hour.)  Controls without a controller for mobile are perfect, it lags some on larger battles but with 50 units on the field it is expected, and it's not terrible lag so that's a bonus. It does take getting use to the tactics though, Unit selection at higher levels and timing is key. Good replay value also. (and if you beat it on normal there is a much harder mode available. Thank god because I love my games  brutally hard.)

The Developers have done a great job maintaining the game. The initial frustration I experienced, in the original release, has been greatly reduced by the introduction of an easy mode.   The premium resource in this game is crystals. These can be obtained by in-app purchase, but, it‚Äôs not necessary if you play enough. The game will reward you with crystals by completing certain tasks, such as defeating 1000 enemies etc. Captured outposts also offer bonuses, such as extra crystals and special units. Most difficulties will become manageable after earning enough crystals and leveling up. The game is very fun and it generally succeeds its' ambitions. The game is definitely of high quality. The gameplay is both accessible and deep. To keep progressing, you will need to attack enemy outposts, defend captured outposts, as well as your own castle. The crystals, better units, additional heroes, and more will come. I have to compliment the great music and the well-executed variety of gameplay.

content: This game goes above and beyond any of the dungeon crawlers that are F2P/P2P. A deep, rich fighting system that reminds me a lot of the later Elder Scrolls games. You can pick melee, ranged, and supplement your fighting style with magic and have an active block. AI for each unit has their own strategy. Some target high health units, and others target range. Very strategic! I only have two gripes. Knights murder the framerates and the leaping spiders deal way too much damage for their crazy spawn rate.
Amazing

I'm updating this review to add a star after playing.  While I still have issue with the game not having a female character choice, very very much have issue, I am now enjoying what the game has to offer for the most part.  The game does delve a bit into pay to win tactics this time around unfortunately and definitely is a bit on the hard side if you don't buy a little IAP currency to get started.  They have random equipment draws to buy and a great many upgrades that all take IAP currency.  You earn it far too slow in game to try to get by without buying a little.  Anyway the game itself is pretty fun to play and added a lot of extras over the last game.  You take over other territories now and gain bonuses from them, but also have to defend them or you lose them back to the monsters.  PvP is completely optional so you don't have to worry about players sacking you.  There is co-op as well which is both really cool and infuriating at the same time (because we are playing online with others but are forced to play males!  Please don't make another game like this without a female hero!).  There are lots of varying skills between the three races, ugh out of room review over early.
